item.title: Oil Hits Fresh High on Supply Deficit Forecasts
item.description: Oil prices rose, with Brent setting a fresh 10-month high as investors anticipated a supply shortfall throughout the rest of the year.

item.title: Dollar Slips as Market Assumes Fed Will Focus on Falling Core Inflation
item.description: U.S. inflation data, which showed headline annual CPI rose slightly more than expected to 3.7%, had only a limited impact on the dollar, which now trades slightly lower, MUFG said, as investors anticipate the Fed to place focus on a slowing trend for the core inflation.

item.title: Metals Mixed Ahead of ECB Rate Decision
item.description: Base metals prices were mixed, while gold edged lower, with Peak Trading saying “the euro comprises 58% of the U.S. dollar index, so today’s ECB policy decision and the currency impact on our commodity markets could be significant.”

item.title: Thyssenkrupp to Reorganize Portfolio, Boost Performance
item.description: Thyssenkrupp said it would merge some businesses into a new unit combining key decarbonization technologies, while also launching a group-wide performance program to help achieve its financial targets.

item.title: Ireland to Conduct Last Government Bond Auction in 2023
item.description: Ireland’s National Treasury Management Agency is heading into its last government bond auction of the year, offering €1 billion in 2027- and 2045-dated bonds and Danske Bank Research recommends being long in Irish government bonds versus EU peers on solid fundamentals.

item.title: Nikkei Rises 1.4%, Led by Real-Estate, Auto Stocks
item.description: Japanese stocks ended higher, led by gains in real estate, auto and electronics shares, as concerns eased about the Fed’s further tightening.

item.title: How the Panama Canal's Drought Is Threatening Global Supply Chains
item.description: The Panama Canal is running out of water, threatening the global supply chains and industries that depend on it. WSJ takes you inside the canal’s operations to understand what this means for the future of this vital shipping route.

item.title: India Keeps Pulling the Plug on Its Digital Economy
item.description: India’s government leads the world in internet shutdowns, cutting off access more than all other nations combined.
